Hukumar Lafiya ta Duniya ta yaba wa gwamnatin kasar Sin kan kokarin da take yi na sarrafa cutar.
WHO ta lura da bambanci tsakanin barkewar cutar SARS ta 2002-2004, lokacin da aka zargi gwamnatin China da yin ɓoye-ɓoye har ta shafi rigakafin da ƙoƙarin sarrafawa, da kuma rikicin na yanzu wanda ya ga gwamnatin tsakiya "ta ba da sabuntawa na yau da kullun don kauce wa tashin hankali kafin hutun Sabuwar Shekarar Sin".
A ranar 23 ga watan Janairu, a martanin da ya mayar wa matakin da gwamnatin tsakiya ta dauka na sanya takunkumin hana zirga-zirga a Wuhan, wakilin WHO Gauden Galea ya bayyana cewa duk da cewa "ba shawarar da WHO ta bayar ba ce", amma kuma "wani muhimmin alama ne ga kudurin da aka dauka na shawo kan annobar a inda ta fi yawa" kuma ya kira ta "marasa misali a tarihin lafiyar jama'a".A ranar 30 ga watan Janairu, biyo bayan tabbatar da kamuwa da cutar daga mutum zuwa mutum a wajen kasar Sin da kuma karuwar adadin wadanda suka kamu da ita a wasu kasashe, WHO ta ayyana annobar a matsayin Matsalar Lafiya ta Duniya (PHEIC), PHEIC ta shida da aka fara yin irin wannan matakin tun lokacin annobar cutar ta alade a shekarar 2009.
Darakta-janar na WHO Tedros Adhanom ya ce PHEIC sakamakon "hadarin yaduwar cutar a duniya musamman ga ƙasashe masu ƙarancin kuɗi da matsakaitan kuɗi ba tare da ingantaccen tsarin kiwon lafiya ba.
A cikin martani game da aiwatar da takunkumin tafiye-tafiye, Tedros ya bayyana cewa "babu wani dalili na matakan da ke hana tafiye-tafiye da cinikayya ta duniya" kuma "WHO ba ta ba da shawarar hana kasuwanci da motsi ba".
